<div id="divhow">    <h2>How it works</h2>    <div class="howitworks-div">        <span class="number">1</span>        <div class="howitworks-point">            <p><img src="./img/howitworks/top100.png">            </p>             <p>An Open Knowledge Maps visualization presents you with a topical overview for your search term.                It is based on the 100 <a class="underline" href="#" data-toggle="popover" data-content="At the moment, we are using the relevance ranking provided by -                         depending on your choice - either the DOAJ API or the PubMed API.                         Both of them mainly use text similarity. PubMed has a detailed                            description of their relevance ranking.">most relevant</a> documents for your search term.            </p>        </div>        <span class="number">2</span>        <div class="howitworks-point">            <p><img src="./img/howitworks/textsimilarity.png">            </p>            <p>We use text similarity to create the knowledge maps.                The algorithm groups those papers together that have many words in common.            </p>        </div>        <span class="number">3</span>        <div class="howitworks-point">            <p><img src="./img/howitworks/headstart-search.png"></p>            <p>The visualization is intended to give you a head start on your                 literature search. You can also use Open Knowledge Maps to stay up-to-date -                 just limit your search to the most recent papers in the options.            </p>        </div>            <!--<p style="font-size: 18px; text-align:center;">For more information please         <a class="underline" target="_blank" href="http://0277.ch/ojs/index.php/cdrs_0277/article/view/157/355">            read this article</a><br>or             <a class="underline" target="_blank" href="https://github.com/OpenKnowledgeMaps/Headstart/blob/master/server/preprocessing/other-scripts/vis_layout.R">check out the explanation of the code</a> on Github.    </p>-->    </div></div>